lucid and probing in these essays , solomon explores in more detail certain topics that he had only been able to touch on more generally in the earlier , full-fledged biography he had written of beethoven . ( he has since followed up more essays strictly on `` late beethoven . '' ) i find these essays thoughtful , probing , and lucid -- not least the fine essay on beethoven 's genuine but ambivalent quest for faith . -- frank burch brow